	<!--
		
		Utility pages are templates for special, unique purposes.
		You can for example set up error pages for error codes 404 and 500, or
		use them for the ecommerce features of OpenSign (product detail, categories, ...).

		When a site is created, OpenSign will also create one instance of each utility page template
		it finds within the template group. Utility pages cannot be deleted or duplicated. Neither
		can a user pick a utility page template to create a page.
		On the other hand utility pages have the very same features as normal page templates, thus 
		can have regions and be edited within OpenSign.

		To set up error pages, the easiest way is to use the most simple page template you have,
		like a simple text page and copy the code into the 404.util file. This way you do not
		need to hardcode the error message but the user can edit it within OpenSign using the
		regions of the template.
	

		Please note:
		Rename this file from ._util to .util if you decide to use it.
		
